1 RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, THE
2 ASSEMBLY CONCURRING, That Rule No. 11 of the Joint Standing
3 Rules of the Senate and Assembly as adopted by the 83rd Session of
4 the Legislature is hereby amended to read as follows:
5 Rule No. 11. Membership and Organization.
6 1. When members of the minority party in the Senate or
7 in the Assembly comprise [one-third or] less than half of the
8 total number elected to that House, minority party
9 membership for that House on the Legislative Commission
10 must be:
11 (a) One, if such membership is less than one-fifth of the
12 total number elected to that House.
13 (b) Two, if such membership is at least one-fifth but [not
14 more] less than [one-third] half of the total number elected to
15 that House.
16  If the [members of the minority party in the Senate or in
17 the Assembly comprise more than one-third of the total
18 number elected to that] membership of a House [, minority]
19 is evenly divided by party , each party’s membership for that
20 House on the Commission must be three . [, being equal to
21 the membership of the majority party.]
22 2. Each House shall select one or more alternate
23 members for each member from that House, designating them
