1 according to party or according to the individual member
2 whom the alternate would replace.
3 3. A vacancy in the regular Senate or Assembly
4 membership created by death or by resignation or by the
5 Legislator’s ceasing to be a member of the Legislature shall
6 be filled by the proper alternate member as designated by that
7 House. If there is no proper alternate member, the Legislative
8 Commission shall fill the vacancy by appointing a Senator or
9 Assemblymember of the same party.
10 4. If for any reason a member is or will be absent from a
11 meeting and there are no alternates available, the Chair of the
12 Commission may appoint a member of the same House and
13 political party to attend the meeting as an alternate.
14 5. The members shall serve until their successors are
15 appointed by resolution as provided in NRS 218E.150, except
16 that the membership of any member who does not become a
17 candidate for reelection or who is defeated for reelection shall
18 terminate on the day next after the election and the vacancy
19 shall be filled as provided in this Rule.
20 6. The Chair shall be selected at the first meeting of the
21 newly formed Legislative Commission and shall serve until
22 his or her successor is appointed following the formation of
23 the next Legislative Commission.
24 And be it further
25 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
26 adoption.
